Things got even more interesting exploring "how far can we push the player rig while inventing playable fantasy races?", then I pitched "if we just added a muzzle, we could get better dragon and catfolk", and THEN the gravity of "WHAT IF THEY WERE KIDS?" hit and all bets were off-

images.alt: An array of bust concepts for fantasy races intended to be playable in the world of Project Dragon. Each concept on this sheet keeps very close in proportion to the base human heads, so they could easily share animations

This sheet shows several of the same playable races from the previous sheet, but reimagined with a muzzle added to the rig. This was intended to pitch to the team "here's how much more variety we could get by stretching our rigging budget to account for these"

A sheet of concepts for each of the races, shows as children. Once these were in game, the appeal of playing a little guy about half the size of a regular player was very evident to everyone on the team

record.text:
We planned to tell the story of our characters through cinematics that were driven by the aesthetics and motifs of their cultures. Leadona & Gran’s intergenerational conflict played out via quilted patchwork!

(And Leadona herself got a revised half mask and cape along the way)

images.alt: A quilted tapestry in the colorful and chaotic style of Leadona- each panel introduces new creatures & cultures from the world of the game. Leadona is keen to change Purran tradition to embrace a new and changing world

A quilted tastefully muted tapestry made by Gran- showing the cycle of generations travelling in caravans around a great wheel- the masks of purran traditional theater at its spokes. Gran represents a call to respect their long established cultural traditions

A revised cape and mask for Leadona's design. The cape has been split into panels for the ease of rigging and animation, and the mask has been adapted to her color scheme as well as to easily conform to fit with the shape of her hat

Just before things started to nosedive on twitter, I posted a thread that walked through the massive body of work I did over the last three years (on an inspiring team) on the cancelled Project Dragon aka Everhaven.
For posterity I reckon I'll repost that thread, piece by piece, over here ✨

images.alt: colorful key splash art for Project Dragon- a group of adventurers (a musical ocarina golem, a rider mounted on a wyvern, a dimunutive cat person and a pet pinoceros) crest a hill over a sun-drenched landscape with billowing clouds and distant ruins. In the sky above, a character composed of constellations spreads their 6 arms and welcomes them to the world.

A screenshot from another social media site with the text "My cats keep pushing each other in my trash can" and it shows two cats taking turns doing exactly as she says - in the photo on the left, it shows the black and white tuxedo cat as the "victor" and his gray tabby "victim" screaming at him from the inside of the trash can, only his face visible. The photo on the right shows the tabby getting the upper hand with the tuxedo cat trying to climb out of the trash can to no avail. Both cats are in nearly the same pose as they lord over their counterparts inside the can in each photo. At least there is symmetry.
